Arizona City Attorney Jon Paladini claims the lone survivor, lookout Brendan McDonough, heard the order from the group's supervisor Eric Marsh and his deputy Jesse Steed .
McDonough told the Arizona Republic that Marsh ordered the crew to leave a safe spot where the fire had already burned .
Paladini says McDonoug came to him to get something 'off his shoulders' and that he was told by his deputy about the move .
The fire killed 19 firefighters in 2013, the worst disaster of its kind since 1933 .